explanation: This solution uses the find function to find the index of the first occurrence of the character ch in the word. If the character is found, it uses the substr function to reverse the prefix of the word and concatenates the rest of the word. If the character is not found, it returns the original word. The time complexity is O(n) because in the worst case, we need to iterate through the entire word to find the character. The space complexity is O(1) because we are not using any extra space that scales with the input size.

